title: Print, "Sultane Reine (The Queen Sultana), plate 29 from Caravanne du Sultan à la Mecque (The Sultan's Caravan to Mecca)", 1748
medium: Black ink on cream laid paper
inscribed: Inscribed across lower margin: Sultane Reine; J.V. del. Sc.
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of Eleanor G. Hewitt
description: Youth in costume of highest ranking and most richly dressed woman in Turkish court. He wears ermine-trimmed robes, high jeweled and feathered turban, necklace and jeweled tasseled belt. Shown facing frontally, landscape beyond.
